## Features
- User registration and login
- Create, read, update, and delete blogs
- Add and retrieve comments
- Real-time communication using Socket.IO
- MySQL database integration with Sequelize


## Start the server:

- npm start

## Usage
Visit http://localhost:5000 to access the home page

## API Endpoints
Users: /users

POST /register: Register a new user
POST /login: Log in a user
GET /allUsers: Get all users
GET /byId/:id: Get user by ID
PUT /update/:id: Update user by ID
DELETE /delete/:id: Delete user by ID
Blogs: /blogs

POST /post: Create a new blog
GET /all: Get all blogs
PUT /update/:blogId: Update blog by ID
DELETE /delete/:blogId: Delete blog by ID
Comments: /comments

POST /addComment: Add a new comment to a blog
GET /all: Get all comments

## Real-Time Communication
Real-time communication is facilitated through Socket.IO for comments

## Database
The application uses MySQL as its database, and Sequelize is employed as the ORM (Object-Relational Mapping).